<BLOCKQUOTE>
The "technical reasons" the take was limited to ten minutes, as viewers of Alfred Hitchcock's "Rope" know, is that film reels were 1000 feet long, or about ten minutes (hence the early nickname for movies as "one reelers," "two reelers," etc.). Actually, 1000 feet can be more like 12 minutes, but it's rounded off in the retelling...</A></B></I>
</BLOCKQUOTE>

